                            <comment id="13540674" author="ashutoshc" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 00:37:05 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;hive&amp;gt; set hive.security.authorization.enabled=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
hive&amp;gt; CREATE TABLE tbl_j5jbymsx8e (key INT, value STRING) PARTITIONED BY (ds STRING);
hive&amp;gt; CREATE VIEW view_j5jbymsx8e_1 as SELECT * FROM tbl_j5jbymsx8e;
hive&amp;gt; DESCRIBE view_j5jbymsx8e_1;
hive&amp;gt; ALTER VIEW view_j5jbymsx8e_1 RENAME TO view_j5jbymsx8e_2;
FAILED: NullPointerException &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13641430" author="teddy.choi" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2013 05:12:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HiveOperation.ALTERVIEW_RENAME was missing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I added it on HiveOperation and SemanticAnalyzerFactory. Also I added a test to reproduce the error as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ashutoshc&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ashutoshc&quot;&gt;ashutoshc&lt;/a&gt; mentioned and it was fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13641432" author="teddy.choi" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2013 05:16:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Review request on &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/10771/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/10771/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13641875" author="ashutoshc" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2013 15:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Few comments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I think you forgot to add .q.out file in your patch.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the .q testcase, can you add set &lt;tt&gt;hive.security.authorization.enabled=false;&lt;/tt&gt; at the end. Otherwise, authorization will be on for rest of the tests as well.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Test TestCliDriver.alter_view_rename.q and TestNegativeCliDriver.recursive_view.q fails after patch. There .q.out file needs to be updated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13642466" author="teddy.choi" created="Fri, 26 Apr 2013 01:15:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ashutoshc&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ashutoshc&quot;&gt;ashutoshc&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;ll update the patch. Thank you for your comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13651535" author="teddy.choi" created="Wed, 8 May 2013 01:31:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Summary of changes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;authorization_8.q.out is included.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;authorization_8.q does not make other tests fail. &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;REVOKE ALL FROM USER hive_test_user; set hive.security.authorization.enabled=false;&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; is appended.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;alter_view_rename.q.out and recursive_view.q.out is updated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
